title: "Big Boost Mondays" by the FINOS Diversity, Equity and Inclusion SIG
description:
Tech Gateway presents - "Big Boost Mondays"

Register on Eventbrite to reserve your place ...
https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/tech-gateway-presents-big-boost-mondays-tickets-537673615257

Building on the great success of last yearâ€™s Tech Gateway events, say hello to â€Big Boost Mondaysâ€, a London DEI meet-up on the last Monday of each month.Â 

Open-source, an open community, open to all for opportunities.

Wï»¿ho is this for?
  • Find out more how open-source is power innovation in finance
  • Hear from leading Women in technology
  • Explore different pathways to a career in technology
  • Industry professionals, senior stakeholders, allies and sponsors
  • Lï»¿BTQ+, Students, under-represented groups, and the curious
  • Nï»¿on-degree holders
  • With local community outreach in Hackney / Tower Hamlets

Hï»¿ow will it work?

Hosted each month by a different FINOS member, opening up their offices to the wider community. Join us to hear from 3 guest speakers - a FINOS Project Maintainer talking about their programs and how to get involved, firms sharing their DEI journey, and organisations from the broader DEI & tech community.

Joining us on the night:

Introducing our hosts Synechron, sharing their DEI journey

"Synechron is an innovative global consulting firm delivering industry-leading digital solutions to transform and empower businesses

"Our workplace culture champions persons of all colors, cultures, backgrounds, beliefs, lifestyles and choices. We recognize and applaud individual differences, and support our employees with multiple programs designed to celebrate and encourage their uniqueness."

Tim Norman -Â Sales Director, will give an introduction to Synechron.

Mathangi Keshavan, Chief of Staff and Diversity & Inclusion UK Lead.

Saamia Ibrahim, Global Operations Lead, at Synechron, will share Synechron and DEI.

Jessica Woodland-Scott -Â Software Engineer @ Deutsche Bank working on Waltz - an open-source enterprise architecture tool.

Topics Jessica will cover;

  • What it's like to work as a engineer in financial services
  • Removing the stigma associated with financial services
  • How Deutsche Bank helped get Jessica into tech & open-source

Raman Rai -Â Product Manager @ PwC UK and part of UK TechWomen100 2022.

Topics Raman will cover;

  • Raman's background and journey into tech
  • Why inclusion is important in tech
  • Types of opportunities in tech - technology degree programmes & other initiatives

Join us each month to:

'Boost your Network, your confidence, your knowledge, your career and your pathway. Big Boost Mondays!

Date â€“ Monday February 27th - 5.30pm Registration & Networking, talks start at 6pm (sharp!), finishing at 6.30pm, with a final 30mins for networking, Q&A and connecting. The event finishes up at 7.00pm!

Register on Eventbrite to reserve your place ...

title: Lloyds Banking Group : DTUK - Open Source - Your Digital Transformation
description:
DTUK - Open Source - Your Digital Transformation

Register on Eventbrite here -Â https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/dtuk-open-source-your-digital-transformation-tickets-533780611177?aff=LI

Step into the world of digital transformation with Lloyds Banking Group at our latest DTUK event. Join our colleagues and expert guest speakers from Red Hat & FINOS delve into our exciting journey with Open Source Software.

Our presentations will cover:

â€¢ Contributing to Digital Transformation at Lloyds Banking Group -Â Sukhvinder Panesar has a passion for enabling and driving the benefits of contributing back to Open Source projects as a Lloyds Banking Group Engineering Lead. In this presentation he'll be taking us through that journey, how Lloyds Banking Group went from consumers to contributors, and what that means for Engineers and the Group.

â€¢ Open Unlocks the Worlds Potential -Â Dean Clark, a Platform Catalyst at Red Hat, is a true evangelist of Open Source. This talk will delve into the Open Culture at Red Hat, the evolution and swift growth of Open Source communities and practices, and demonstrate how Open Source continues to unleash the world's potential, one commit at a time.

â€¢ Open Source in Financial Services and Regulatory Engineering -Â Get an overview of the state of the Open Source movement in financial services as well as hear where the community is today from James McLeod, FINOS Director of Community. You will learn about the opportunities, and quirks, of a fast-growing movement that has the potential to revolutionize the very fabric of financial services and regulatory engineering. This talk is highly recommended for developers, stakeholders and the curious who are looking to adopt and grow their Open Source offerings within the financial services industry.

About the Open Source Mission at Lloyds Banking Group

The Open Source Mission is here to provide comprehensive resources and support, ensuring safe and effective Open Source Software (OSS) implementation. We collaborate with colleagues throughout Lloyds Banking Group to align the approach of implementing and contributing to OSS. Our partnership with FINOS and its members is an exciting next step in our transformation, and a step into the wider Open Source Community.

#engineerthefuture

title: (community) FSI Hackathon for Autism
description:
Find out more from Peter Smulovics hereÂ ğŸ‘€

Registration information

If you are among the companies or individuals already pre-registered by domain/name, just visit theÂ registration URLÂ and log in with existing account or apply for a new account. If you are not, please do drop a note toÂ Michelle.Ng@ey.comÂ to add your companyâ€™s domain to the listÂ ğŸ™‚Â You can sign up as an individual or as a group. You will be aligned with a use case and a team and provided training resources if you need to prepare you for the event.

Mission Statement

Bring developers from the Financial Services industry together to demonstrate how innovative Microsoft technologies can transform autism treatment by tackling real world use cases provided by families and creating lasting open-source projects for the community.

What does the Hackathon entail? It is:

  • 2 days
  • 70+ developers
  • 5 use cases
    • And infinity possibility to help people with using your technology skills!

Background

The first Financial Services Autism Hackathon was held in 2018 founded by Leo Junquera, working at Microsoft at the time, and Peter Smulovics from Morgan Stanley, as a grass roots effort to combine the unique value proposition of Microsoft (technology innovation) with the technology talent which exists in Financial Services, and direct it towards an industry in dire need of technology innovation.

Dates and Location

The date of the event is April 19-20th. It is a hybrid event, with the in-person venue in New York City at the EY Wavespace.

Who should sign up?

It is a combination of roles that are filled by participants like yourself who make the hackathon successful each year.Â 

  • Developers Work for the digital transformation to demonstrate the power how new technologies can be applied to the issues facing the autism community.
  • UX Designers People with Autism see the world differently â€“ help them see the world! Design interfaces, interaction patterns, both in the digital and in the physical world, that enables them to overcome the differences and to participate in the digital transformation of the autism community!
  • Business Analysts Translate the use cases gathered from families with autistic children, behaviorists in the field, experts in the community, and service providers to enable better interaction between the parties, provide hallway test cases, helping finding the voice, to make the results presentable.

title: FINOS Open Source London Meetup - Hosted by Nomura, London
description:
We're delighted to be holding our first in-person Open Source London event of 2023 at Nomura, who have kindly offered to host the event!

***

IMPORTANT: In order to comply with Nomura's security procedures and gain admittance to the event, it is imperative that:

  • you register your place on Eventbrite, providing your full name
  • you bring photographic ID to the event

***

We're excited to announce two confirmed talks, and we're in the process of confirming another:

// Harnessing the power of open source to achieve industry-wide data standardisation for capital markets //

  • Ffion AclandÂ â€“ Executive Director, Data Engineer atÂ Goldman Sachs
  • Ian SloyanÂ â€“ Senior Advisor Data & Digital Solutions at theÂ ISDA
  • Gabriel CallsenÂ â€“ Director, FinTech and Digitalisation at theÂ ICMA

Data is the lifeblood of many industries but it plays a vital role in financial services and particularly in the capital markets world.

As the industry drastically accelerates the pace of open collaboration, join ISDA, ICMA and Goldman Sachs for an exploration of theÂ Common Domain ModelÂ andÂ Financial Objects SIGÂ from an open source engineering and business benefits perspective.

During this joint presentation ISDA, ICMA and Goldman Sachs will take the Open Source London group on a tour of the Common Domain Model whilst exploring the business and engineering benefits of the FSI standardising financial objects by leveraging the CDM through FINOS platforms likeÂ Legend, maintained by Goldman Sachs.

// How to Be a Good Corporate Citizen in Open Source //

  • Dawn Foster, Director of Open Source Community Strategy withinÂ VMwareâ€™s OSPO

Collaboration in open source projects is important for companies, but it can be difficult to strike the right balance between the needs of the company and the open source project. This can create friction and put pressure on employees who participate on behalf of their company when the needs of the individual, the company, and the community are not aligned. This talk will focus on ways to create this alignment and help all of us be successful together.

Communities are a critical component of open source projects, and the way that people participate can reflect positively or negatively on the person and organisation that they represent. The majority of work in some projects, like Kubernetes, is done by people working for a wide variety of organisations, and the success of many projects requires participation from these companies.

The talk contains three sections:

  • Dynamics of collaboration in open source projects between individuals, companies, and communities.
  • Strategies for participating in ways that will benefit your company, your employees, and the community.
  • Tips for being a good corporate citizen as you contribute to open source projects.

***
If you are interested in presenting, please contact Claire Cocks (marketing@teams.scottlogic.com). We particularly welcome talk submissions from women speakers, speakers from ethnic minorities, and speakers from other under-represented groups.

***
By registering for the event in person or online, you agree to abide by our Code of Conduct which you can find in the 'About' section:Â https://www.meetup.com/open-source-london/

title: FINOS Banks Only Open Source Round Table
description:
FINOS invites you to a FINOS Banks Only Open Source roundtable that's taking place to coincide with the FINOS BMO Hackathon in NYC on 3/4 May. Location in person in New York and virtually on Zoom.Â Â Zoom will be provided for international guests.Â Â 

The roundtable will take place underÂ Chatham House Rule, meaning participants are free to use the information received during the roundtable, but neither the identity nor the affiliation of the speaker(s), nor that of any other participant, will be revealed.

Also, in the essence of openness, anonymisedÂ content from the roundtable could be repurposed for use withinÂ Open Source Readiness. The content will be published by the FINOS team and will exclude the participant's details under Chatham House Rule.

Discussion Topics: Please vote on the issue below to help us choose a topic:Â https://github.com/finos/open-source-readiness/issues/118

I hope you find this opportunity as exciting as the FINOS team and we're looking forward to seeing you on the day.

Hackathon NYC 3/4 May


Finally, as I mentioned above, this round table is to coincide with the FINOS Members-Only Hackathon. Hackathon details here:Â Â https://www.finos.org/hosted-events/2023-05-03-member-exclusive-hackathon-bmo. Please get in touch if your organisation has developer staff in NYC and you think they might be interested in attending.Â  Â Â 


Kind regards,

Rob

title: Big Boost Mondays - Dublin, Ireland - Sponsored by Microsoft
description:
Join us for our next "Big Boost Mondays" Dublin event at Microsoft on Monday 15th May!

Lï»¿ive and in-person @ï»¿ Microsoft Ireland, South County Business Park, One Microsoft Place, Carmanhall and Leopardstown, Dublin, D18 P521, Ireland.

Register here -Â https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/tech-gateway-presents-big-boost-mondays-dublin-microsoft-tickets-610949044037

Open-source, an open community, open to all for opportunities.

Wï»¿ho is this for?

  • Find out more how open-source is power innovation in finance
  • Hear from leading Women in technology
  • Explore different pathways to a career in technology
  • Industry professionals, senior stakeholders, allies and sponsors
  • Lï»¿BTQ+, Students, under-represented groups, and the curious
  • Nï»¿on-degree holders
  • With local community outreach in Dublin / Ireland



Hï»¿ow will it work?

Hosted each month by different tech firms, opening up their offices to the wider community.Â 

Join us on the night you can hear from 3 guest speakers talking about their programs, initiatives and how to find your pathway into tech! Alongside firms sharing their DEI journey, and the importance of building a diverse workforce within the tech industry.

Aï»¿bout our host on the night;

Martina Naughton -Â Global Partner Sales Director @ Microsoft Ireland.

Martina believes that her best work is done at the intersection between technology, innovation, and sustainability. Her long career in the IT Industry has always been inspired by her passion for finding technology solutions for the most pressing challenges facing business and society.

She believes that building trust with her teams, partners and customers is the foundation to a successful business. Leading with integrity, purpose and impact & has a proven track record of winning new business and driving revenue growth in highly complex and competitive environments.



Jï»¿oining us on the night;

Martina NaughtonÂ - Global Partner Sales Director @ Microsoft Ireland.

Microsoft Corporation is an American multinational technology corporation headquartered in Redmond, Washington. Microsoft's best-known software products are the Windows line of operating systems, the Microsoft Office suite, and the Internet Explorer and Edge web browsers.

Topics Martina will cover;

  • Her journey into tech
  • Importance of diversity, equity & inclusion in the workplace
  • Tips & advice into how to get started into technology

Jeevantika Lingalwar -Â Cloud Solution Architect & D&I Gender Pillar Lead @ Microsoft Ireland & Founder of International Women in Tech

Jeevantika Lingalwar has a wide background in tech and plays an active role in bringing together diversity in tech. A few of her achievements include:

Award Winner

  • WomenTech Global Ambassador Award of the year 2021

Featured

  • Featured In an article/magazine as young women in tech Rising Star by AOTMP

Award Finalist

  • Woman of the Year award 2021
  • Mentor of the Year award 2021
  • Community award of the year 2021

Jeevantika is very passionate about Women in Technology and Diversity & Inclusion. She founded International Women in Tech group and is leading a community of more than 4500 amazing members. Jeevantika is very determined to help and motivate young minds, she is a mentor to 60 young kids aged 8-15 years and teaches them about â€œFuture in/of AIâ€. Jeevantika also has her own free mentorship program called as â€œCoffee chat with Jeevantikaâ€ Jeevantika is a mentor to international university students in Ireland. Jeevantika is also nominated for various women in tech leadership awards in Ireland.

An entrepreneur, leader, and a Tech speaker Jeevantika is passionate about helping others grow and share her experience and knowledge with everyone.Â 

Topics Jeevantika will cover on the night;

  • Her personal journey into tech
  • International Women in Tech - how & why she grew a community of women in tech from 10 to 4.7k+ members
  • Microsoft DEI initiatives + tips & advice to those wanting to get into tech

Clare Dillon -Â Executive Director @ InnerSource Commons Foundation

Clare has over 25 years' experience of leadership development, business strategy, and technology evangelism. Clare has helped organisations maximise the opportunities presented by the latest trends in technology. She is an advocate of open source and InnerSource (the use of open source methods to create proprietary code) & is passionate about how technology is changing and shaping the world we live and work in.

Topics Clare will cover on the night;

  • Her personal journey into tech
  • Open-Source
  • How to get started in Technology



Join us each month to:

'Boost your Network, your confidence, your knowledge, your career and your pathway. Big Boost Mondays!

@ï»¿ ï»¿ Microsoft Ireland, South County Business Park, One Microsoft Place, Carmanhall and Leopardstown, Dublin, D18 P521, Ireland.

/// Seating is limited! You Must Register Here To Attend:Â https://www.finos.org/hosted-events/2023-05-01-osinfsi-meetup-finos-open-house-nyc

Don't miss out on theÂ May 1st OSinFinance Meetup: FINOS Strategic Initiatives Open HouseÂ - seating is limited! Join us to discover how you can contribute to and reap the rewards of FINOS' strategic initiatives on open regulation, open source readiness, and desktop interoperability (FDC3).

Date:Â Monday May 1

Meetup Name:Â FINOS Strategic Initiatives Open House

Location:Â Synechron - 11 Times Square, NYC, 10036 (Microsoft Building) - Entrance on 8th Avenue between West 41st and West 42nd Street
/// Seating is limited! You Must Register Here To Attend:Â https://www.finos.org/hosted-events/2023-05-01-osinfsi-meetup-finos-open-house-nyc

Important Timings:

  • 5.30pm open doors to public
  • 6.30pm talks start
  • 7.45pm talks conclude
  • 7.45pm - 8.15pm Networking at Synechron
  • 8.30pm Networking at Beer Authority

Talk Topics - Details On Specifics Coming Soon:
Open Source Readiness:

  • We launched the Open Source Readiness Initiative to support financial services organizations in their open source maturity journey, so they can realize the benefits of open source code and collaboration.
  • Open Source Readiness is leading activities that enable safe and compliant open source consumption and contribution in financial services firms.

Open Regulation Innovation:

  • The Open RegTech Initiative explores and promotes opportunities for open collaboration between financial institutions, technology firms, service providers, and regulators. It aims to use open source standards and software to change how financial regulation is implemented and supervised.

Interoperability / FDC3:

  • Interoperability and FDC3 aim to provide an open standard for interoperability on the financial desktop. This includes standardized verbs to invoke actions between applications (called "intents"), a standardized data format, an OpenAPI app directory standard, and standardized API operations.

title: Global Accessibility Awareness Day Hackathon
description:
FINOS Global Accessibility Awareness Day Hackathon

https://www.finos.org/hosted-events/2023-05-18-gaad-hackathon

Overview of Hack:

Starting April 24th, and judging the week of May 15-18.

Financial Institutions need to manage the balance between risk compliance, user experience and, accessibility inclusion when developing digital solutions (mobile, web). Web Accessibility (or e- Accessibility) pertains to the design of websites and mobile applications that do not present barriers of access to people with disabilities or disorders. The development of these digital solutions need to consider accessibility compliance along the entire production workflow from design, to development, to printing/rendering.

Click here for GAAD Hack FAQ

Purpose of the Hack:

The purpose of this hackathon is to promote the design of accessibly inclusive digital and physical financial assets and tools. Specifically:

  • Bring attention to the end-to-end collaboration challenges between designers and developers as it relates to risk compliant accessibility solutions.
  • Explore the uses cases for where accessibility inclusion is applicable to Financial Institutions.

For Sponsors:

We are currently soliciting sponsors for existing and new challenges. The deadline to become a sponsor isÂ March 15th, 2023. Please fill out the form below to express your interest in becoming a sponsor!

Click here for GAAD Hack Sponsor Overview
Click here for GAAD Hack Sponsor 1 pager

For Participants:

Teams of 1-4 will work over 2.5 weeks to develop end to end solutions centered around accessibility. Please see the following documents for more information:

Prizes include:

  • Cash prizes!
  • SWAG
  • Fall/Summer Internships
  • Access to FINOS collaboration spaces for incubation of ideas
  • FINOS spotlight blog post

Click here for GAAD Hack Participant 1 pager
Click here for GAAD Hack Flyer

Challenges

Atomic Accessibility Design Challenge

Sponsor:Â Discover Financial Services
Challenge Details:Â Context: Given the challenges associated with risk compliance for people with disabilities (Visual, Motion, Motor, Auditory, Cognitive/Learning), Atomic Design enables designers and developers to establish a round-trip workflowÂ process that traverses from abstract concepts to concrete details. The application of Atomic Design concepts towards the development of accessibly compliant solutions yields consistency and scalability while mitigating regulatory risk. Problem: Organize a well- rounded team that can leverage new accessibility tools to develop an end-to-end solution that explores novel applications of accessibility technologies for financial services.
Supporting Technology:Â Atomic Accessibility Design Theme Builder GitHub Repo

Â 

More challenges to come soon!


Please register your interest for sponsorship and/or participation using our link here:Â 

bit.ly/41RytVA
